  "doc_id": "60731",
  "text": "Here, we analyse the spatial and temporal variation of repeated migratory journeys by adult marsh harriers Circus aeruginosus along the whole migratory route. Our study is the first, to our knowledge, to present a strictly comparable analysis of repeatability in routes and timing of animal migration, assessing the variation within and between individuals. This allows us to explore current hypotheses about route recapitulation (as shown for homing pigeons Columba livia [CITATION_1] ) and consistent migratory schedules (as shown for bar-tailed godwits Limosa lapponica baueri [CITATION_2] ) for a long-distance migrant.",
